1.title: Huskystarcraft
1.plot: Husky visits home after being away at school. While going through an old childhood box of his belongings Husky finds an original "Game Genie" video game cartridge. After attempting to clean it a giant red man appears, it is the real life incarnation of the Game Genie. The Game Genie grants Husky one video game-related wish, which Husky chooses as having the ability to quick save his life and go back in time. 2.title: TheWarpZone
2.plot: Some time between getting his new power and going to the party, Husky is seen dropping the Game Genie cartridge on his front lawn. Two unsuspecting people passing by (Davis and Odom) find the Game Genie and release him once again. Being granted a wish, they decide to have the ability to unlock achievements throughout their daily lives. While highly entertaining at first, the achievements quickly begin to be the focus of their lives. 3.title: PressHeartToContinue
3.plot: Some time shortly before Odom and Davis are pulled over from Episode 2, they accidentally throw the Game Genie cartridge out the window while trying to summon the Game Genie to get out of the mess they're in. Unable to stop and retrieve the cartridge, a new passer-by finds it lying on the ground. Dodger, after remembering the cartridge from her child hood, makes the same mistake as all the other previous characters, and summons the Game Genie. 4.title: LaynePavoggi
4.plot: Shortly after Dodger is seen exploding, Layne finds the Game Genie cartridge laying outside the wreckage. Attempting to clean the cartridge, Layne also summons the Game Genie. Layne decides to pick the 'Level Select' wish. Attempting to test his new power, Layne teleports himself to the old Wild West. Immediately upon arriving in the Wild West, Layne meets a local gunslinger who also oddly resembles the Game Genie. 5.title: Finale
5.plot: Right before Husky is run over, Layne uses his level select power to get himself out of Hell and to save him. Having pushed Husky out of the way, Davis and Odom do not run over him, but recognize him as they pass and quickly pull over. Husky, having almost been run over, tries to make sense of what is happening. Upon realizing that their problems are revolving around the Game Genie they try to figure out a way to end it.
